# Richtato - Personal Finance Management Platform

## Project Overview

Richtato is a comprehensive personal finance management application for tracking expenses, income, budgets, and net worth. It features bank account syncing (Teller/Plaid), AI-powered transaction categorization, and interactive dashboards.

## Tech Stack

- **Backend**: Django 5.x, Django REST Framework, PostgreSQL, Gunicorn
- **Frontend**: React 19, TypeScript, Vite 7, Tailwind CSS, Shadcn/UI
- **Infrastructure**: Docker, Nginx (single-container deployment)
- **Integrations**: Teller (bank sync), Plaid (bank sync), OpenAI (AI categorization)

## Architecture

### Backend Pattern: Repository → Service → View

```
Views (HTTP handling) → Services (business logic) → Repositories (database access)
```

- **Views**: Thin HTTP wrappers, delegate to services
- **Services**: Business logic, calculations, orchestration
- **Repositories**: ORM queries, data access only

### Frontend Pattern: Pages → Components → API Services

```
Pages (routes) → Components (UI) → lib/api/* (API calls) → Contexts (state)
```

- **pages/**: Route-level components
- **components/**: Reusable UI components (organized by feature)
- **lib/api/**: API service classes (transactions, auth, dashboard, etc.)
- **contexts/**: React Context for global state (Auth, Preferences)

## Development Commands

```bash
# Start all services
docker compose up -d

# View logs
docker compose logs -f backend
docker compose logs -f frontend

# Restart after code changes
docker compose restart backend frontend

# Run Django shell
docker compose exec backend python manage.py shell

# Run migrations
docker compose exec backend python manage.py migrate
```

## Database Models (Core)

| Model | Purpose |
|-------|---------|
| `User` | Extended Django user with preferences |
| `FinancialAccount` | Bank accounts, credit cards, investment accounts |
| `Transaction` | All financial transactions (debit/credit) |
| `TransactionCategory` | Hierarchical categories with type (income/expense/transfer) |
| `CategoryKeyword` | Keywords for auto-categorization |
| `Budget` | Budget periods with category allocations |
| `BankConnection` | Teller/Plaid connection credentials |

## API Structure

```
/api/v1/
├── /auth/              # Login, logout, demo user
├── /transactions/      # CRUD transactions, categories
├── /accounts/          # Financial accounts
├── /budget/            # Budget management
├── /budget-dashboard/  # Budget analytics
├── /asset-dashboard/   # Net worth, metrics, trends
├── /sync/              # Bank sync (Teller, Plaid)
└── /user/              # Profile, preferences, category settings
```

## Key Files

### Backend
- `backend/richtato/settings.py` - Django configuration
- `backend/richtato/urls.py` - Root URL routing
- `backend/config/categories_defaults.yaml` - Default category definitions
- `backend/apps/*/views.py` - API endpoints
- `backend/apps/*/services/*.py` - Business logic
- `backend/apps/*/repositories/*.py` - Database queries

### Frontend
- `frontend/src/App.tsx` - Root component with routing
- `frontend/src/components/Layout.tsx` - Main layout with sidebar
- `frontend/src/contexts/AuthContext.tsx` - Authentication state
- `frontend/src/lib/api/*.ts` - API service classes

## Conventions

- **Logging**: Use `loguru.logger` (backend), avoid `console.log` (frontend)
- **Icons**: Lucide React icons
- **Styling**: Tailwind CSS utilities, use `cn()` for conditional classes
- **State**: React Context for global, useState for local
- **API Calls**: Async/await with try-catch, CSRF tokens for mutations

